As Deanna wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/09/2004 at 18:28:00 (Eastern Time),
>Thank you that does help, but my next question is how to write an 
>equation, in standard form, containig the given points
>
>Example-- (5,3); (1,4)
>
>How do I complete this type of equation?
>
>Thanks again!

Hi Deanna,

First, use the two points to find the slope (which is the ratio of the
change in y to the change in x, or 'rise over run').  Then you have
two points and a slope; and you just saw how from one point and a
slope, you can find the equation. 

